ing students may enjoy several periods of travel before the academic year begins, during holiday periods and after the completion of the program. To apply for a study abroad or exchange opportunity, please contact the UNT Study Abroad office. EXTERNAL MUSIC STUDENTSStudents wishing to do an exchange at UNT must also: apply to UNT Study Abroad Office submit the music information questionnaire by the month of May, prior to your arrival APPLICATION TIPSApply through the UNT Study Abroad Office. If you are a UNT student, begin by attending one of their weekly workshops. (Sage Hall 236) studyabroad.unt.edu, studyabroad@unt.edu) Undergraduate UNT Music majors should consult with Ms. Jessie Niu, Academic Counselor,  throughout this process. STUDY ABROAD with UNT - UNT courses that will take you away!UNT students should tell their Academic Advisor that they are interested studying abroad. WHAT STUDENTS SAYStudy Abroad Blog, Barcelona Spain photos, Stockholm Sweden trip blog and photos WHERE WILL YOU GO  Hungary-AustriaUNT Music Ed Study AbroadFall Semester More information UK Britain— University of Leeds (Pay UNT Tuition. Room and board paid in Britain.)www.leeds.ac.uk Czech Republic Janacek Music Academyhttp://english.jamu.cz/Semester or year. Pay UNT tuition and UNT room and board. SwedenRoyal College of Music in Stockholm(Folk Music, Jazz, Classical Music, Music Education, Composition, Conducting, Music & Media Production)www.kmh.se SpainBarcelona— Liceu Music Conservatoryhttp://www.conservatoriliceu.es/Semester or year. Pay UNT Tuition. Room and board paid in Spain. GhanaSummer TaiwanTaipei— National Taiwan Normal University (NTNU)www.ntnu.edu.tw/Semester or year. Pay UNT Tuition. Room and board paid in Taiwan. AustriaVienna – IES (study abroad provider)www.IESabroad.com   (Liberal Arts, Music majors, Music electives)   Amalfi Coast Music Festival — summer program opportunitieshttp://www.amalfi-festival.org/Local contact: Carol Wilson-COM Voice Faculty MORE OPTIONS RECIPROCAL INTERNATIONAL EXCHANGE PROGRAMS UNT students trade places, literally, with a music student from another country to participate in one of these exchanges! AFFILIATED PROGRAMSSeparate providers, collaborating with UNT Global Learning offer resources and opportunities for studying abroad.  Some providers of affiliated programs:www.goinglobal.com/en/ (Institute for the International Education of Students)www.iie.org (Institute of International Education – includes Gilman Scholarship)www.studyabroad.comhttp://www.iesabroad.org/study-abroad/programs National Student Exchange (NSE) Trade places with a student from a US institution-member of NSE programs. www.unt.edu/nse/ Q&AWhat music courses can I take during my exchange at UNT? Contact the College of Music Advising Office for more information. How long is an exchange? One semester or one academic year. How much does it cost? Depends on the specific program. Most exchange programs charge tuition at the rate of your home institution. Some programs include housing.  Scholarships, Funding Resources? Check with the course provider. UNT provides a scholarship to outbound students. Many affiliated providers offer scholarships to their participants.Also see http://www.moneygeek.com/education/college/resources/study-abroad/ and http://www.accreditedschoolsonline.org/resources/study-abroad/ Visit Us Music Building 415 Avenue C Denton, TX 76201 Mail Us University of North Texas 1155 Union Circle #311367 Denton, TX 76203-5017 Contact Us 940-565-2791 music.information@unt.edu Technical issues? Site last updated on May 09, 2017 Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA| Privacy| Electronic Accessibility| State of Texas Online| Emergency Preparedness| THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information| UNT Compliance Hotline| Governors Committee on People with Disabilities| Texas Veterans Portal| UNT Home Site last updated on May 09, 2017 | Important Links 